# max-migrate project

Module for **migrating bot/channel workflows from Telegram to the Max messenger**.

## Stack

- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Runtime:** Node.js 22
- **Max library:** `@maxhub/max-bot-api` (official client)
  - Repo: https://github.com/max-messenger/max-bot-api-client-ts
  - Install: `npm install @maxhub/max-bot-api`

## Documentation

- **Max bots (JS/TS):** https://dev.max.ru/docs/chatbots/bots-coding/library/js
- **Max messenger docs on Context7:** https://context7.com/websites/dev_max_ru — **use for Max API questions** (@Docs or context7).

## Max Bot API baseline

```typescript
import { Bot } from '@maxhub/max-bot-api';

const bot = new Bot(process.env.BOT_TOKEN);

bot.command('start', (ctx) => ctx.reply('Welcome!'));
bot.on('message_created', (ctx) => ctx.reply(ctx.message.body.text));

bot.start();
```

Events: `bot_started`, `message_created`, `message_edited`, `message_removed`, `bot_added`, `bot_removed`, `user_added`, `user_removed`, `chat_title_changed`, `message_callback`. Sending: `ctx.reply()`, `bot.api.sendMessageToUser()`, `bot.api.sendMessageToChat()`. For methods without wrappers — `ctx.api.raw.get/post/put/patch/delete`.

## Project goals

When porting logic from Telegram to Max, account for API differences (events, message types, attachments, keyboards). Cross-check Max docs on Context7 and dev.max.ru.
